text: Truly the best briyani ive ever tasted in the west side. Everytime i think of briyani, this is the place to go. They sell out really quickly, so hurry!

Make sure to stand in front of the stall and wait for your food. They will always FORGET due to overwhelming orders.
Their food is good hence why by midday they are shut. But that is also why they dont take customer service seriously. Ppl will always buy regardless.

I confidently recommend this shop as the best for biryani and Indian cuisine in Bukit Panjang. I've been a loyal customer since my first taste of their dishes. Keep in mind that the biryani often sells out quickly, so don't delay.

Simply the best nasi briyani in Singapore. I tried dum chicken, mutton briyani. The briyani rice is so fluffy, delicious, packed with lovely spice smell,and not oily.

Love the prata kosong too. The fish curry, mutton curry and chicken curry are so delicious to go with the prata. yum...

Bought 3 kosong pratas (2+1)for takeway. Then decided to eat one of them at the hawker so went ask for a small bowl of curry but stall refused to give??!!!! Saying 2 pratas can only give 1 curry? 1 prata kosong is $1.10 yet they refused to give even a small bowl of curry??
Anyway, will never return as stall assistant was very rude.
If they can only give one curry for every 2 pratas then they should indicate as there is no minimum pieces of pratas needed. Very selfish and money minded hawkers üòè
